 Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + time_of_perils_exit + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 14 time_of_perils_exit → 16 living_in_simulation → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJy9WG1P28gW%2FitH6O7ehA3BzitJL1eiJexWl7YIqKpVqdKJPUlmsT2%2BMzYh26W%2FfZ8Z24lDjBop0n5BwZ55znPez%2FG3A59PWRokb6TPD4YHx8d0enpKt4qJiBJJnmJ%2FLvFjEdFd2nLcDi2kCvwHwRe0cMetcXfcG%2FfHbmfs9sZun2o6kTG5%2FbqBuYsAd6Z1GsaJkBF5c6AOyaGYKenNBQsMqDtokUtTpsZswZbjeRqySBcvWsQiEbJAj7UM%2BWLOkuJNl6ZpkiqeXxiHLEm4Gi9EMh%2F7QnsyjRIRzYrjPYpk%2Bfl443Zxqr8Sl8OxcSBXIqF9IkI%2BltNxzJXAKf4o1m97FIgHAy2isRZhGjCrdfG6T7ikZTRm0yn3LAdjRmukEfPmxNaWEpoYXS2TOX5PRcAJ3li%2F1seUGEsw39cNUhwuFBHXJJUFU%2FwIBmYhhwJC43ky55nt%2F61htMizGK%2FIk2EstbHR6gDuRj4HIh4JbdF0wiKfBTLiFCJGgiZ9XYXA6OGroWqu88cYSuHiAwtSTnJqEdbR0rRgr7lOaJIuKTVizEXNy4oN6WauRBjTJx4gIjhdKfkHcLPbv47ej67PbkfnNFnSjEdcsYQ342URmtyHN8pmOsTLBhyfZGSMJYFksT5GHleJUTmUCoG4spjOzmbmYHEcCK6bdLMMm4GcRVIhOmrf4m6D4kH3qW6xrLcGzk%2F05u0re3LCE5Y9jZWcsIkIRAIiE2nU9k1efXYa5H5p0gXzEgmZ0DWDwoHY%2BCBKGqQlcRMYUs3gudHnxfnZ5e%2FH%2F%2FpCEx7IBVLG3LUe5o%2F4HSxxHdiwqsWCbD%2F1